Ques 40  Quality of Service (QoS) determines how reliably a message is delivered between the publisher and subscriber.
QoS 0: At most once
Message is sent only once.
No acknowledgement is received.
Fastest but messages may be lost.

QoS 1:  At least once
Sender waits for an acknowledgment (ACK).
If no ACK is received, the message is retransmitted.
Guarantees delivery, but duplicate messages are possible.

QoS 2:  Exactly once
Uses a four-step handshake.
Ensures the message is delivered exactly once.
Most reliable but has the highest communication overhead and latency.

For a water level monitoring system, QoS 1 is the best choice according to me because 
The reading for the monitoring system is important and should reliably reach the cloud.

Ques 49  Top 5 Security Vulnerabilities: 
1. Hardcoded Wi-Fi SSID and Password
The Wi-Fi network name (SSID) and password are directly written into the source code.
Anyone with access to the code can see the credentials.
If the code is uploaded to GitHub, the credentials become publicly accessible.
Attackers can connect to the Wi-Fi network and access other devices.
What we can do is store credentials in a separate config.h file.
Add config.h to .gitignore.

2. Using HTTP Instead of HTTPS
Data travels without encryption. Attackers can intercept or modify sensor data.
We can use HTTPS instead of HTTP and validate the server certificate.

3. Public MQTT Broker Without Authentication
Sensor data is published to a public MQTT broker without a username or password.
Anyone can subscribe to the topic and read sensor data and data integrity cannot be guaranteed.
Use a private MQTT broker. Enable username/password authentication.

4. No Validation of Incoming Commands
The device accepts every incoming MQTT message or HTTP command without checking its contents.
Malicious users can send unexpected commands thus device behavior can be manipulated.
Accept only predefined commands to be on the safer side.

5. No Encryption or Secure Communication
Commands sent to the IoT device can be altered and sensitive information may be exposed.
Use TLS/SSL encryption/Use HTTPS for web communication.



